# Speculum — frontend standards

Before UI/UX work under `web/`, read and obey:

1. `docs/frontend-standards.md`
2. `docs/frontend-patterns.md`
3. `web/README.md`
4. `docs/naming.md` (motor feature folders)
5. `docs/engineering-standards.md` still applies (tests, CI, wire, V1)

## Hard bans

- **shadcn only** — extend `web/src/components/ui/`; never install MUI/Fluent/Ant/Chakra or invent a parallel look.
- No god pages/components — split into `*Flow` / `*Step` / `*Section` / sub-routes (~350 LOC soft cap; investigate >500).
- No JSON/text walls as primary UI — complex data/flows need visualization facilitators (table+detail, timeline, overview→tabs, health strip).
- No information saturation — **revealing UI**: primary path first; Advanced / Sheet / drill-down on progress.
- No thin CRUD when enrichment (wizard, disclosure, viz) is required.
- No raw hex in Admin/Setup — use `@theme` tokens (`web/src/index.css`).
- No silent failures / toast-only errors on config pages — explicit loading/empty/success/error.
- No W7S in operator-facing labels.

## Enrichment

Prefer value-adding facilitators: wizards, Sheets, Tabs (one job), tables+detail, timelines, status strips, AlertDialog for destructive work. Copy recipes from `docs/frontend-patterns.md` — do not invent competing patterns.

## Diff hygiene

Minimal scope; match local conventions; add missing shadcn primitives on first need rather than one-off custom widgets.
